    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened, then, slice the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely and chop the<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 600ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1.2L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
